o 2004 qualification]]\n|-\n|22.\n|16 October 2002\n|[[Millennium Stadium]], Cardiff, Wales\n|{{fb|Wales}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1'''&nbsp;\u2013 1\n|align=\"center\" |1\u20132\n|[[UEFA Euro 2004 qualifying Group 9|UEFA Euro 2004 qualification]]\n|-\n|23.\n|11 June 2003\n|[[Helsinki Olympic Stadium]], Helsinki, Finland\n|{{fb|Finland}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |2\u20130\n|[[UEFA Euro 2004 qualifying Group 9|UEFA Euro 2004 qualification]]\n|-\n|24.\n|6 September 2003\n|[[Stadio Giuseppe Meazza]], Milan, Italy\n|{{fb|Wales}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''4'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |4\u20130\n|[[UEFA Euro 2004 qualifying Group 9|UEFA Euro 2004 qualification]]\n|-\n|25.\n|8 September 2004\n|[[Stadionul Republican]], Chi\u015fin\u0103u, Moldova\n|{{fb|Moldova}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |1\u20130\n|[[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 5|2006 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n|26.\n|1 March 2006\n|[[Stadio Artemio Franchi]], Firenze, Italy\n|{{fb|Germany}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''4'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |4\u20131\n|[[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n|27.\n|4 July 2006\n|[[Westfalenstadion]], Dortmund, Germany\n|{{fb|Germany}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |2\u20130\n|[[2006 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Semi-finals|2006 FIFA World Cup]]\n|}\n\n=== Records ===\n* All-time appearances for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics#Appearances|Juventus]] in all competitions (705 appearances)<ref name=\"calciomercato.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/altre-notizie/juventus-del-piero-vs-mihajlovic-512508 |title=Juventus, Del Piero: Due gol... per Mihajlovic &#124; Altre notizie |publisher=Calciomercato.com |language=Italian |date=4 February 2014}}</ref>\n* Second most appearances for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics#Appearances|Juventus]] in [[Serie A]] (478 appearances)<ref name=\"calciomercato.com\"/><ref 