y#Most goals from a penalty kick|Third highest goalscorer from penalties in Serie A]] (50)<ref name=\"90min.com\"/>\n* [[Football records in Italy#Most goals from a free kick|Third highest goalscorer from free kicks in Serie A]] (22)<ref name=\"Pirlo eyes Mihajlovic record\"/>\n* Italian all-time top scorer from free kicks in all competitions (52 goals: 46 goals at club level, 6 goals with the Italy national team).<ref name=\"7 Alessandro Del Piero\"/><ref name=\"Alessandro Del Piero\"/>\n* Italian player with the most seasons with 10 goals or more across all club competitions (17 seasons)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Juventus/24-04-2011/record-fedelissimo-80959586614.shtml|title=Record da fedelissimo, Ma Del Piero \u00e8 amaro|website=gazzetta.it|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=24 April 2011}}</ref>\n* Most goals scored by an Italian international as a substitute (5)<ref name=\"GOL DALLA PANCHINA\"/>\n* [[Italy national football team#Top goalscorers|Joint fourth highest goalscorer for Italy]] (27 goals, alongside [[Roberto Baggio]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.figc.it/nazionali/Marcatori?squadra=1&mode=|title=FIGC: Classifica Marcatori|publisher=FIGC|language=Italian|accessdate=29 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130731000359/http://www.figc.it/nazionali/Marcatori?squadra=1&mode=|archive-date=31 July 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n\n=== Club ===\n'''Juventus'''<ref name=\"Alessandro Del Piero: Palmares\">{{cite web|url=http://en.alessandrodelpiero.com/profile/palmares.html|title=Alessandro Del Piero: Palmares|website=alessandrodelpiero.com|accessdate=13 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Senior squad'''\n*[[Serie A]]: [[1994\u201395 Serie A|1994\u201395]], [[1996\u201397 Serie A|1996\u201397]], [[1997\u201398 Serie A|1997\u201398]], [[2001\u201302 Serie A|2001\u201302]], [[2002\u201303 Serie A|2002\u201303]], ''[[2004\u201305 Serie A|2004\u201305]]''{{refn|This title was revoked through the courts following the [[2006 Italian football scandal|Calciopoli scandal]].|name=\"calciopoli\"|group=\"nb\"}}, ''[[2005\u201306 Serie A|2005\u201306]]'' {{refn|name=\"calciopoli\"|group=\"nb\"}}, [[2011\u201312 Serie A|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Serie B]]: [[2006\u201307 Serie B|2006\u201307]]\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[1994\u201395 Coppa Italia|1994\u201395]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[1995 Supercoppa Italiana|1995]], [[1997 Supercoppa Italiana|1997]], [[2002 Supercoppa Italiana|2002]], [[2003 Supercoppa Italiana|2003]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[1995\u201396 UEFA Champions League|1995\u201396]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[1996 UEFA Super Cup|1996]]\n*[[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]: [[1996 Intercontinental Cup|1996]]\n*[[UEFA Intertoto Cup]]: [[1999 UEFA Intertoto Cup|1999]]\n\n'''Primavera squad'''\n*[[Torneo di Viareggio]]: [[1994 Torneo di Viareggio|1994]]\n*[[Campionato Nazionale Primavera]]: 1993\u201394\n\n=== International ===\n'''Italy'''<ref name=\"Alessandro Del Piero: Palmares\"/>\n*[[FIFA World Cup]]: [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]]\n\n=== Individual ===\n* [[European Sports Magazines#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]]: [[European Sports Media#1995.E2.80.9396|1995\u201396]], [[European Sports Media#1996.E2.80.9397|1996\u201397]], [[European Sports Media#1997.E2.80.9398|1997\u201398]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/esm-xi.html|title=ESM XI|website=rsssf.com|publisher=RSSSF|accessdate=13 April 2015}}</ref>\n* [[UNICEF]] European Footballer of the Season: 1995\u201396<ref>{{cite web|url=https://footballgreatones.files.wordpress.com/2017/06/ksuf-92.pdf|title=Best European footballers by season|publisher=Ukrainian Football|author1=Volodymyr Banyas|date=25 August 2015|accessdate=2 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823170312/https://footballgreatones.files.wordpress.com/2017/06/ksuf-92.pdf|archive-date=23 August 2017|url-status=dead}} ([[Ukrainian language|ukr.]])</ref>\n* [[Most Valuable Play