 of Juventus F.C. records and statistics#All-time top 10 goalscorers|Juventus]] (290 goals: 186 goals in open play, 62 goals from penalties, 42 goals from free-kicks)<ref name=\"calciomercato.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juworld.net/giocatori-statistiche-gol.asp?idgiocatore=623 |title=Alessandro Del Piero: statistiche gol fatti \u2013 Juworld.NET \u2013 Juventus World: il portale dei tifosi Juventini |publisher=Juworld.NET |date=}}</ref>\n* All-time decisive goals holder for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics|Juventus]] (135)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Juventus/19-10-2011/del-piero-conto-rovescia-803358827348.shtml|title=Del Piero, conto alla rovescia, Tutti i record che pu\u0148 battere|website=gazzetta.it|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=19 October 2011}}</ref>\n* Second most minutes played holder for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics|Juventus]] (48,363)<ref name=\"en.alessandrodelpiero.com\">{{cite web|url=http://en.alessandrodelpiero.com/profile/my-number.html |title=I numeri di Alessandro Del Piero |publisher=En.alessandrodelpiero.com |date=}}</ref>\n* Second most appearances for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics|Juventus]] in the [[Supercoppa Italiana]] (6 appearances)<ref name=\"calciomercato.com\"/>\n* Second most appearances for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics|Juventus]] in the [[UEFA Champions League]] (92 appearances)<ref name=\"calciomercato.com\"/>\n* Second most appearances for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics#Appearances|Juventus]] in [[UEFA club competition records and statistics|UEFA club competitions]] (124 appearances)<ref name=\"Presenze Giocatori\">{{cite web|url=http://www.myjuve.it/statistiche-giocatori-juventus/riassunto_presenze.aspx|title=Presenze Giocatori|trans-title=Player appearances|publisher=My Juve.it|language=Italian|accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref>\n* Most appearances for [[List of Juventus F.C. records and statistics#Appearances|Juventus]] in international club competitions (130 appearances)<ref name=\"Presenze Giocatori\"/>\n* [[Supercoppa Italiana#All-time top goalscorers|Second most goals scored in the Supercoppa Italiana]], alongside [[Samuel Eto'o]], [[Andriy Shevchenko]], and [[Carlos Tevez]] (3)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/alltime_goalgetter/ita-supercoppa/tore/1/|title=All-time top goalscorers|publisher=worldfootball.net}}</ref><ref name=myjuve.it>{{cite web|url=http://www.myjuve.it/statistiche-giocatori-juventus/classifica-reti_segnate-supercoppa_italiana-SI.aspx|title=Juventus F.C. Giocatori, Statistiche: Reti nella Supercoppa Italiana|publisher=My Juve.it|language=Italian|accessdate=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n* Most goals scored in a single season by a [[Sydney FC]] player (14)<ref name=\"footballaustralia.com.au\">{{cite web|url=http://www.footballaustralia.com.au/sydneyfc/news-display/del-piero-ready-to-break-record-on-sunday/60381|title=Del Piero Ready To Break Record on Sunday \u2013 Sydney FC \u2013 Sydney FC 2014|publisher=Footballaustralia.com.au|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Football records in Italy#Most goals from a penalty kick|Third highest goalscorer from penalties in Serie A]] (50)<ref name=\"90min.com\"/>\n* [[Football records in Italy#Most goals from a free kick|Third highest goalscorer from free kicks in Serie A]] (22)<ref name=\"Pirlo eyes Mihajlovic record\"/>\n* Italian all-time top scorer from free kicks in all competitions (52 goals: 46 goals at club level, 6 goals with the Italy national team).<ref name=\"7 Alessandro Del Piero\"/><ref name=\"Alessandro Del Piero\"/>\n* Italian player with the most seasons with 10 goals or more across all club competitions (17 seasons)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Juventus/24-04-2011/record-fedelissimo-80959586614.shtml|title=Record da fedelissimo, Ma Del Piero \u00e8 amaro|website=gazzetta.it|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=24 April 2011}}</ref>\n* Most goals scored by an Italian international as a substitute (5)<ref name=\"GOL DALLA PANCHINA\"/>\n* [[Italy national football team#Top goalscorers|Joint fourth highest goalscorer for Italy]] (27 goals, alongside [[Roberto Baggio]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.figc.it/nazionali/Marcatori?squadra=1&mode=|title=FIGC: Classifica Marcatori|publisher=FIGC|language=Italian|accessdate=29 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130731000359/http://www.figc.it/nazionali/Marcatori?squadra=1&mode=|archive-date=31 July 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n\n=== Club ===\n'''Juventus'''<ref name=\"Alessandro Del Piero: Palmares\">{{cite web|url=http://en.alessandrodelpiero.com/profile/palmares.html|title=Alessandro Del Piero: Palmares|website=alessandrodelpiero.com|accessdate=13 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Senior squad'''\n*[[Serie A]]: [[1994\u201395 Serie A|1994\u201395]], [[1996\u201397 Serie A|1996\u201397]], [[1997\u201398 Serie A|1997\u201398]], [[2001\u201302 Serie A|2001\u201302]], [[2002\u201303 Serie A|2002\u201303]], ''[[2004\u201305 Serie A|2004\u201305]]''{{refn|This title was revoked through the courts following the [[2006 Italian football scandal|Calciopoli scandal]].|name=\"calciopoli\"|group=\"nb\"}}, ''[[2005\u201306 Serie A|2005\u201306]]'' {{refn|name=\"calciopoli\"|group=\"nb\"}}, [[2011\u201312 Serie A|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Serie B]]: [[2006\u201307 Serie B|2006\u201307]]\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[1994\u201395 Coppa Italia|1994\u201395]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[1995 Supercoppa Italiana|1995]], [[1997 Supercoppa Italiana|1997]], [[2002 Supercoppa Italiana|2002]], [[2003 Supercoppa Italiana|2003]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[1995\u201396 UEFA Champions League|1995\u201396]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[1996 UEFA Super Cup|1996]]\n*[[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]: [[1996 Intercontinental Cup|1996]]\n*[[UEFA Intertoto Cup]]: [[1999 UEFA Intertoto Cup|1999]]\n\n'''Primavera squad'''\n*[[Torneo d